# Atlas Business Rules Workflow

**Source of truth:** `docs/BUSINESS_RULES.md` (BR-001 … BR-024+). Treat it as part of Atlas architecture.

**Decision engine:** `backend/core/businessRulesEngine.js` — business rules only, no conversation wording.

## Before coding

1. Read `docs/BUSINESS_RULES.md` before architectural or behavioral decisions.
2. Check whether an existing BR-XXX already covers the feature. Follow it if yes.
3. If no rule exists, recommend a new BR-XXX instead of inventing behavior.
4. If a request conflicts with a rule, **stop and name the conflict** (e.g. "Conflicts with BR-008") before implementing.

## While coding

- Reference BR numbers in comments/docs when applicable: `// Implements BR-004`
- Do **not** duplicate business logic. Reuse engines: Business Rules, Conversation, Scheduling, Capacity, Response Builder; Presence when it exists.
- If logic repeats across features, recommend an engine refactor before adding more code.

## After a sprint

Include a brief summary: files modified, engines affected, BRs implemented, new BRs recommended, technical debt (if any).

Full workflow: `docs/DEVELOPMENT_WORKFLOW.md`
